## 2. Main Troubleshooting Flowchart

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start: git clone fails] --> B[Check exact error message]
    B --> C{Is the URL correct?}
    C -- No --> C1[Get correct repo URL from GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket and retry]
    C -- Yes --> D{Can DNS resolve host?}
    D -- No --> D1[Run nslookup github.com / cat /etc/resolv.conf / fix DNS]
    D -- Yes --> E{Can network reach host?}
    E -- No --> E1[Run ping github.com / curl -I https://github.com / check firewall VPN proxy]
    E -- Yes --> F{Using HTTPS or SSH?}

    F -- HTTPS --> G{Authentication failed?}
    G -- Yes --> G1[Use Personal Access Token instead of password]
    G -- No --> H{SSL or proxy error?}
    H -- Yes --> H1[Check CA certs, proxy config, curl, git config]
    H -- No --> I{Repo not found?}
    I -- Yes --> I1[Verify repo path and access permissions]
    I -- No --> J{Large repo / EOF / index-pack / slow network?}
    J -- Yes --> J1[Try shallow clone, re-run on stable network, check disk]
    J -- No --> K[Check local path permissions and existing directory]

