## 3. Step-by-Step Troubleshooting Tree With Commands

### Step 1: Verify the repository URL

Common error:
```bash
fatal: repository 'https://github.com/user/repo.git/' not found
```

Debug:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git
```

Checks:
- Is the owner name correct?
- Is the repo name correct?
- Is the repo private?
- Are you logged in with the correct account?

Fix:
- Copy the clone URL directly from the repository page
- For private repos, ensure your account has access

---

### Step 2: Check DNS resolution

Common error:
```bash
fatal: unable to access 'https://github.com/...': Could not resolve host
```

Debug:
```bash
nslookup github.com
getent hosts github.com
cat /etc/resolv.conf
```

What it means:
- Your system cannot resolve the domain name into an IP

Fix:
- Check internet connection
- Use working DNS servers
- Restart networking if needed
- Fix `/etc/resolv.conf` if broken

---

### Step 3: Check basic internet and HTTPS reachability

Common errors:
```bash
Failed to connect to github.com port 443
Connection timed out
```

Debug:
```bash
ping github.com
curl -I https://github.com
traceroute github.com
```

What it means:
- Network path is blocked or unstable
- Firewall, VPN, or proxy may be interfering

Fix:
- Try another network
- Disable broken VPN/proxy
- Check firewall rules
- If on corporate network, ask whether GitHub is blocked

---

### Step 4: Determine whether you are using HTTPS or SSH

Check URL format:
```bash
# HTTPS
https://github.com/user/repo.git

# SSH
git@github.com:user/repo.git
```

Why this matters:
- HTTPS errors are usually token/proxy/SSL related
- SSH errors are usually key/agent/port/access related

---

## 4. HTTPS Clone Troubleshooting

### 4.1 Authentication failed

Common error:
```bash
fatal: Authentication failed for 'https://github.com/...'
```

Debug:
```bash
git config --global --get credential.helper
```

What it means:
- Password authentication is not accepted
- Token is wrong, expired, or missing

Fix:
- Use a Personal Access Token instead of password
- Clear cached bad credentials and re-authenticate

Useful commands:
```bash
git credential reject
printf "protocol=https\nhost=github.com\n" | git credential reject
```

Retry:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git
```

---

### 4.2 SSL certificate problem

Common error:
```bash
SSL certificate problem: unable to get local issuer certificate
```

Debug:
```bash
curl -Iv https://github.com
git config --global --get http.sslVerify
```

Fix:
```bash
sudo yum install ca-certificates -y
sudo update-ca-trust
```

Temporary test only:
```bash
git -c http.sslVerify=false clone https://github.com/user/repo.git
```

Do not disable SSL permanently unless you fully understand the risk.

---

### 4.3 Proxy problems

Common errors:
```bash
Proxy CONNECT aborted
Received HTTP code 407 from proxy after CONNECT
```

Debug:
```bash
env | grep -i proxy
git config --global --get http.proxy
git config --global --get https.proxy
```

Remove wrong proxy:
```bash
git config --global --unset http.proxy
git config --global --unset https.proxy
unset http_proxy
unset https_proxy
unset HTTP_PROXY
unset HTTPS_PROXY
```

Set correct proxy if needed:
```bash
git config --global http.proxy http://user:pass@proxy:port
git config --global https.proxy http://user:pass@proxy:port
```

---

## 5. SSH Clone Troubleshooting

### 5.1 Permission denied (publickey)

Common error:
```bash
Permission denied (publickey).
fatal: Could not read from remote repository.
```

Debug:
```bash
ssh -T git@github.com
ssh-add -l
ls -la ~/.ssh
```

Generate key:
```bash
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "you@example.com"
```

Start agent and add key:
```bash
eval "$(ssh-agent -s)"
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
```

Show public key:
```bash
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
```

Fix:
- Add the public key to your Git hosting account
- Ensure the correct account is used

Retry:
```bash
ssh -T git@github.com
git clone git@github.com:user/repo.git
```

---

### 5.2 Host key verification failed

Common error:
```bash
Host key verification failed.
```

Debug and fix:
```bash
ssh-keygen -R github.com
ssh -T git@github.com
```

What it means:
- Stored host fingerprint does not match current server key
- Often caused by stale `known_hosts` entry

---

### 5.3 SSH timeout / port 22 blocked

Common error:
```bash
ssh: connect to host github.com port 22: Connection timed out
```

Debug:
```bash
nc -vz github.com 22
ssh -vT git@github.com
```

Fix option 1: Use HTTPS
```bash
git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git
```

Fix option 2: Use SSH over port 443

Create or update `~/.ssh/config`:
```sshconfig
Host github.com
  Hostname ssh.github.com
  Port 443
  User git
```

Test:
```bash
ssh -T git@github.com
```

---

## 6. Repository Access and Permission Issues

### 6.1 Repository not found

Common reasons:
- Repo name is wrong
- Repo is private
- You do not have permission
- Wrong organization account

Debug:
```bash
git ls-remote https://github.com/user/repo.git
git ls-remote git@github.com:user/repo.git
```

What it means:
- If `ls-remote` fails, your URL or access is wrong

Fix:
- Verify repo path
- Confirm access with owner
- Use the correct GitHub account or SSH key

---

### 6.2 SSO / organization restrictions

Possible symptoms:
- Access denied despite valid credentials
- Repo visible in browser but clone fails

Fix:
- Authorize your token or SSH key for the organization
- Ensure SSO is enabled for your account if required

---

## 7. Local Machine and Filesystem Issues

### 7.1 Destination path already exists

Common error:
```bash
fatal: destination path 'repo' already exists and is not an empty directory.
```

Fix:
```bash
rm -rf repo
git clone <repo_url>
```

Or:
```bash
git clone <repo_url> new-folder
```

---

### 7.2 Permission denied creating working tree

Common error:
```bash
fatal: could not create work tree dir 'repo': Permission denied
```

Debug:
```bash
pwd
ls -ld .
touch testfile
```

Fix:
```bash
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /path/to/parent
```

Or clone into a writable directory:
```bash
cd ~
git clone <repo_url>
```

---

### 7.3 Disk full

Common error:
```bash
No space left on device
```

Debug:
```bash
df -h
du -sh .
```

Fix:
- Free disk space
- Remove old files
- Clone into a larger filesystem

---

## 8. Large Repo / Pack / Transfer Issues

### 8.1 early EOF / index-pack failed / RPC failed

Common errors:
```bash
fatal: early EOF
fatal: index-pack failed
error: RPC failed
```

Debug:
```bash
GIT_TRACE=1 GIT_CURL_VERBOSE=1 git clone <repo_url>
```

Fixes:
```bash
git clone --depth 1 <repo_url>
git config --global core.compression 0
```

Sometimes also helpful:
```bash
git config --global http.version HTTP/1.1
```

What it means:
- Connection unstable
- Proxy breaks large transfers
- Repo is large and clone is timing out

---

### 8.2 Slow clone or hanging clone

Debug:
```bash
GIT_TRACE=1 git clone <repo_url>
top
iostat
```

Fix:
- Check CPU, RAM, disk I/O
- Try shallow clone
- Try off VPN
- Try on stable internet

---

## 9. Git Installation / Version / Config Issues

### 9.1 Git too old

Debug:
```bash
git --version
```

Fix on RHEL-like systems:
```bash
sudo yum update git -y
```

Why it matters:
- Older Git may have TLS or HTTP issues with modern servers

---

### 9.2 Broken Git config

Debug:
```bash
git config --list --show-origin
```

Look for:
- wrong proxy
- wrong sslVerify
- broken credential helper
- bad url rewrite

Common cleanup:
```bash
git config --global --unset http.proxy
git config --global --unset https.proxy
git config --global --unset http.sslVerify
git config --global --unset credential.helper
```

---

## 10. Debug Commands for Deep Inspection

### Enable verbose Git tracing

For HTTPS:
```bash
GIT_TRACE=1 GIT_CURL_VERBOSE=1 git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git
```

For SSH:
```bash
GIT_SSH_COMMAND="ssh -vvv" git clone git@github.com:user/repo.git
```

These show:
- DNS lookup path
- proxy use
- TLS handshake
- SSH key negotiation
- remote server responses

